obile-center px3"\n         style="max-width:720px;">\n      <div class="flex items-start justify-between mobile-flex-column mobile-justify-center mobile-items-center">\n        <h1 class="fs42 m0 font-bold mobile-fs24 mb2">Mapillary CrowdDriven Dataset</h1>\n      </div>\n      <p class="fs20 gray m0 font-regular mobile-mt3">\n        A benchmark for visual localization in outdoor scenes. The dataset contains pairs of image sequences with ground truth poses obtained through human annotation of control points, depicting urban and suburban scenes with challenging appearance and viewpoint changes. Read the corresponding <a href="https://research.mapillary.com/publication/iccv21" class="text-decoration-none" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">publication</a> for more details.\n      </p>\n      <p class="black fs16 m0 pt3 pb2"\n         style="max-width:440px;">\n        This Mapillary CrowdDriven Dataset\n        <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/"\n          target="_blank"\n          rel="noopener noreferrer"\n          class="text-decoration-none">\n          Creative Commons Attribution NonCommercial Share Alike (CC BY-NC-SA)\n        </a>\n        license.\n      </p>\n      <dataset-download-request\n        style="max-width:440px;"\n        [datasetName]="\'CrowdDriven\'"\n        [datasetType]="\'crowd_driven\'">\n      </dataset-download-request>\n    </div>\n    <div class="bg-white black rounded py24 px3 mt3"\n         style="box-shadow: 0px 4px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1); max-width: 512px">\n      <div class="mb2 black fs16 bold">Features</div>\n\n      <div class="flex items-center mb2">\n        <i class="circle-checkmark icon-16 neon-green mr1"></i>\n        <span>Ground truth alignment obtained through human annotation and QA of control points. Annotation tool <a href="https://github.com/mapillary/OpenSfM/tree/feat_annotation_ui" class="text-decoration-none" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">open-sourced</a> (<a href="https://github.com/mapillary/OpenSfM/blob/feat_annotation_ui/doc/source/annotation_tool.rst" class="text-decoration-none" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">docs</a>)</span>\n      </div>\n      <div class="flex items-center mb2">\n        <i class="circle-checkmark icon-16 neon-green mr1"></i>\n        Three difficulty categories: easy (where traditional SfM works), medium (some SOTA methods work) and hard (almost no SOTA methods can relocalize)\n      </div>\n      <div class="flex items-center mb2">\n        <i class="circle-checkmark icon-16 neon-green mr1"></i>\n        Extreme lighting (day / night) and viewpoint (opposite direction) changes in the harder categories.\n      </div>\n      <div class="flex items-center mb2">\n        <i class="circle-checkmark icon-16 neon-green mr1"></i>\n        39 Locations, ~2.5k images.\n      </div>\n      <div class="flex">\n        <a href="https://research.mapillary.com/"\n           class="ResearchLink flex items-center text-decoration-none black">\n          Brought to you by Mapillary Research\n          <i class="inline-block icon-24 arrow-right neon-green"\n             style="margin-left:4px"></i>\n        </a>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<div class="Container1200 flex items-center justify-between mobile-flex-column mx-auto px3 py4">\n  <div>\n    <img src="/dataset/assets/images/ICCV21.png">\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<div class="Container1200 mx-auto px2 mb4">\n  <div class="black fs32 font-bold mb40">More about the dataset</div>\n  <div class="flex items-start justify-between mobile-flex-column fs16 black">\n    <div style="max-width: 540px;">\n      Visual localization is the problem of estimating the position and orientation from which a given image (or a sequence of images) is taken in a known scene. It is an important part of a wide range of computer vision and robotics applications, from self-driving cars to augmented/virtual reality systems.\n      <br><br>\n      Visual localization techniques should work reliably and robustly under a wide range of conditions, including seasonal, weather, illumination and man-made changes. Recent benchmarking efforts model this by providing images under different conditions, and the community has made rapid progress on these datasets since their inception. However, they are limited to a few geographical regions and often recorded with a single device.\n    </div>\n    <div class="mobile-mt3"\n         style="max-width: 540px;">\n      We propose a new benchmark for visual localization in outdoor scenes, using crowd-sourced data to cover a wide range of geographical regions and camera devices with a focus on the failure cases of current algorithms. Experiments with state-of-the-art localization approaches show that our dataset is very challenging, with all evaluated methods failing on its hardest parts. As part of the dataset release, we provide the tooling used to generate it, enabling efficient and effective 2D correspondence annotation to obtain reference poses.\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<dataset-footer></dataset-footer>\n',styles:[CZ()]})],My);var DZ=C(219),SZ=C.n(DZ);let Ry=class{};Ry=Ie([$t({selector:"metropolis",template:'<header style="margin-bottom:84px">\n  <div class="Header fixed gray bg-white fixed z2 top-0 left-0 right-0 bg-transparent">\n    <div class="Container1200 height-100 px24 mx-auto flex flex-auto justify-between items-center font-regular h3">\n      <a class="flex-none mapillary-logo dark"\n         href="/"></a>\n\n      <a href="https://www.mapillary.com"\n         class="btn btn-raised flex items-center font-semi-bold rounded border-beautiful-gray h4">\n        mapillary.com <i class="chevron-right gray i5 ml1"></i>\n      </a>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</header>\n\n<div class="LandingBackground bg-cover bg-center black font-regular">\n  <div class="Container1200 px24 mx-auto flex items-center justify-between mobile-flex-column tablet-flex-column width-100">\n    <div class="flex flex-column mobile-center"\n         style="padding-right: 90px;">\n      <div class="flex items-start justify-between mobile-flex-column mobile-justify-center mobile-items-center">\n        <h1 class="fs42 m0 font-bold mobile-fs24 mb2">Mapillary Metropolis Dataset</h1>\n      </div>\n      <p class="fs20 gray m0 font-regular mobile-mt3">\n        A multitask benchmarking framework comprising complementary data modalities at a city-scale size, registered across different representations, and enriched with human and machine generated annotations.\n      </p>\n      <p class="black fs16 m0 pt3 pb2">\n        This Mapillary Metropolis Dataset is provided under the\n        <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/"\n          target="_blank"\n          rel="noopener noreferrer"\n          class="text-decoration-none">\n          Creative Commons Attribution NonCommercial Share Alike (CC BY-NC-SA)\n        </a>\n        license.\n      </p>\n      <dataset-download-request\n        [datasetName]="\'Metropolis\'"\n        [datasetType]="\'metropolis\'">\n      </dataset-download-request>\n    </div>\n    <div class="bg-white black rounded py24 px3 mt3"\n         style="box-shadow: 0px 4px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1); max-width: 512px">\n      <div class="mb2 black fs16 bold">Features</div>\n\n      <div class="flex items-center mb2">\n        <i class="circle-checkmark icon-16 neon-green mr1"></i>\n        27,745 high-resolution 360\xb0 images with human-curated annotations\n      </div>\n      <div class="flex items-center mb2">\n        <i class="circle-checkmark icon-16 neon-green mr1"></i>\n        3D point clouds from: aerial and street-level LIDAR,\n        Structure-from-Motion and Multiview-Stereo reconstructions,\n        geo-anchored based on high-precision, survey-grade ground control points\n      </div>\n      <div class="flex items-center mb2">\n        <i class="circle-checkmark icon-16 neon-green mr1"></i>\n        Full aerial image cover with 7.5 cm/px resolution\n      </div>\n      <div class="flex items-center mb2">\n        <i class="circle-checkmark icon-16 neon-green mr1"></i>\n        Manually labeled 2D / 3D object annotations for up to 39 semantic categories\n      </div>\n      <div class="flex items-center mb2">\n        <i class="circle-checkmark icon-16 neon-green mr1"></i>\n        Human annotated aerial-to-ground correspondences\n      </div>\n      <div class="flex items-center mb2">\n        <i class="circle-checkmark icon-16 neon-green mr1"></i>\n        Registered CAD models, machine-generated panoptic segmentation masks and more...\n      </div>\n      <div class="flex">\n        <a href="https://research.mapillary.com/"\n           class="ResearchLink flex items-center text-decoration-none black">\n          Brought to you by Mapillary Research\n          <i class="inline-block icon-24 arrow-right neon-green"\n             style="margin-left:4px"></i>\n        </a>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<div class="Container1200 mx-auto px2 my4">\n  <video autoplay\n         loop\n         muted\n         playsinline\n         #video\n         (canplay)="video.play()"\n         (loadedmetadata)="video.muted = true"\n         style="width:100%">\n    <source type="video/mp4"\n            src="/dataset/assets/metropolis/metropolis_video.mp4" />\n  </video>\n</div>\n\n<div class="Container1200 mx-auto px2 mb4">\n  <div class="black fs32 font-bold mb40">More about the dataset</div>\n  <div class="flex items-start justify-between mobile-flex-column fs16 black">\n    <div style="max-width: 540px;">\n      Mapillary Metropolis is a city-scale, multi-modality benchmarking dataset for researching and evaluating computer vision algorithms in the context of 3D semantic map making.\n      <br><br>\n      It forms a comprehensive benchmark suite unifying heterogeneous data sources, including images from street-level and airborne perspectives, LiDAR scans from street-level and aerial views, CAD model information, and surveying grade ground control points for precise geo-localization.\n    </div>\n    <div class="mobile-mt3"\n         style="max-width: 540px;">\n      We provide both human- and machine-generated annotations as well as correspondences for selected object categories across all data modalities where present.\n      <br><br>\n      The availability of such a wide, registered set of data types enables benchmarking of object recognition (2D/3D and tracking), 3D reconstruction, SLAM, image-based depth estimation, relocalization, image- and patch-based matching, image retrieval, depth estimation, etc.\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<div class="Container1200 mx-auto mb4 px24">\n  <app-steps [bigDotsSpace]="true"\n             [darkActiveDot]="true"\n             [lightGreyDots]="true">\n    <app-step class="mb2">\n      <div class="flex items-center justify-center width-100">\n        <img class="SlideImage"\n            src="/dataset/assets/metropolis/MVSPano.jpg" />\n      </div>\n    </app-step>\n    <app-step class="mb2">\n      <div class="flex items-center justify-center width-100">\n        <img class="SlideImage"\n            src="/dataset/assets/metropolis/DetectionPano.jpg" />\n      </div>\n    </app-step>\n    <app-step class="mb2">\n      <div class="flex mobile-flex-column items-center width-100"\n        style="justify-content: space-evenly;">\n        <div class="flex flex-column mobile-mt3">\n          <img class="SlideImage"\n            src="/dataset/assets/metropolis/MVSAerial.jpg" />\n        </div>\n        <div class="flex flex-column">\n          <img class="SlideImage"\n            src="/dataset/assets/metropolis/DetectionFrontCam.jpg" />\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </app-step>\n  </app-steps>\n</div>\n\n<div class="Container1200 mx-auto px2 mb4">\n  <div class="mx-auto center"\n      style="max-width: 540px;">\n    <div class="black fs32 font-bold mb40">Mapillary Metropolis SDK</div>\n    <div class="fs16 black">\n      <a class="text-decoration-none"\n        target="_blank"\n        rel="noopener noreferrer"\n        href="https://github.com/mapillary/metropolis_sdk">This SDK</a>\n        is intended as a collection of examples to get you started\n        with understanding the Mapillary Metropolis dataset,\n        e.g. by visualizing annotations or performing common queries on the data.\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<dataset-footer></dataset-footer>\n',styles:[SZ()]})],Ry);var TZ=C(308),MZ=C.n(TZ);let Oy=class{};Oy=Ie([$t({template:'<mpsd-header activeLink="citation"></mpsd-header>\n<section id="citation">\n  <div id="citation-top"\n       class="flex items-center flex-column mx-auto px3 py3 md-py4 width-100"\n       style="max-width: 840px">\n    <h1 class="fs42 font-bold black mt0">Citation</h1>\n    <div id="citation-content"\n         class="md-mt4 flex flex-column">\n      <div id="citation-paper"\n           class="mb3 mx-auto">\n        <a href="https://research.mapillary.com/img/publications/ECCV20a.pdf"></a>\n        <div></div>\n        <div></div>\n        <div></div>\n      </div>\n      <div class="md-ml4">\n        <h2 class="fs24 black font-bold mt0">Mapillary Planet-Scale Depth Dataset</h2>\n        <p class="gray">\n          M. Lopez Antequera, P. Gargallo, M. Hofinger, S. Rota Bul\xf2, Y. Kuang, and P. Kontschieder. Mapillary Planet-Scale Depth Dataset.\n          <br />\n          Proceedings of the European Conference on Computer Vision (ECCV)\n        </p>\n        <div class="flex">\n          <a href="https://research.mapillary.com/img/publications/ECCV20a.pdf"\n             class="text-decoration-none neon-green font-semi-bold">Research paper</a>\n          <div class="VerticalSeparator mx2"></div>\n          <a href="https://research.mapillary.com/img/publications/ECCV20a.bib"\n             class="text-decoration-none neon-green font-semi-bold">bib</a>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</section>\n<footer class="da