nc-sa/4.0/"\n          target="_blank"\n          rel="noopener noreferrer"\n          class="text-decoration-none">\n          Creative Commons Attribution NonCommercial Share Alike (CC BY-NC-SA)\n        </a>\n        license.\n      </p>\n\n      <dataset-download-request\n        [datasetName]="\'Mapillary Planet-Scale Depth\'"\n        [datasetType]="\'mpsd\'">\n      </dataset-download-request>\n\n    </div>\n    <div class="bg-white black rounded py24 px3 mobile-mt3 mb1"\n         style="box-shadow: 0px 4px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1); max-width: 512px">\n      <div class="mb2 black fs16 bold">Features</div>\n\n      <div class="flex items-start mb1">\n        <i class="circle-checkmark icon-16 neon-green mr1 mt2"></i> The most diverse dataset for depth estimation with metric depth information with 750,000 images\n      </div>\n      <div class="flex items-center mb1">\n        <i class="circle-checkmark icon-16 neon-green mr1"></i> 50,000 image clusters cover varying geographical areas globally\n      </div>\n      <div class="flex items-center mb1">\n        <i class="circle-checkmark icon-16 neon-green mr1"></i> Images captured with more than 100 different camera models\n      </div>\n      <div class="flex items-center mb3">\n        <i class="circle-checkmark icon-16 neon-green mr1"></i> Diverse outdoor scene characteristics\n      </div>\n      <div class="flex">\n        <a href="https://research.mapillary.com/"\n           class="ResearchLink flex items-center text-decoration-none black">\n          Brought to you by Mapillary Research\n          <i class="inline-block icon-24 arrow-right neon-green"\n             style="margin-left:4px"></i>\n        </a>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<div class="Container1200 flex items-center justify-between mobile-flex-column mx-auto px3 pb4">\n  <div class="mobile-mt3 mr3"\n       style="max-width: 540px">\n    <img src="/dataset/assets/mpsd/map.png">\n  </div>\n  <div class="mobile-mt3"\n       style="max-width: 540px">\n    <img src="/dataset/assets/mpsd/depth-map.png">\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<div class="Container1200 mx-auto px3 pb160 pt3">\n  <div class="black fs32 font-bold mb3 mobile-fs24">More about this dataset</div>\n  <div class="flex items-start justify-between mobile-flex-column fs16 black">\n    <div style="max-width: 540px;">\n      Mapillary Planet-Scale Depth (MPSD) is a novel dataset providing training data for monocular depth estimation. The dataset is generated by running monocular Structure-from-Motion and multi-view stereo to obtain dense depth for eligible images.\n      <br><br>\n      Our dataset, containing images from all over the world, is larger, more complex and diverse than any previously published depth dataset.\n    </div>\n    <div class="mobile-mt3"\n         style="max-width: 540px;">\n      It currently contains approximately 750,000 images, extracted from over 50,000 individual 3D reconstructions captured by a broad range of camera types with different focal lengths and distortion characteristics, in a broad set of environments and weather conditions, seasons, times of day, viewpoint and with real noise and motion patterns.\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<dataset-footer></dataset-footer>\n\n<app-fullscreen-modal [closeable]="true"\n                      [isOpen]="requestModalOpen$ | async"\n                      (close)="closeRequestForm()">\n  <section class="px2 mx-auto"\n           style="max-width: 566px;">\n    <h2 class="font-semi-bold center px2 h1 mb3">\n      Download the Mapillary Planet-Scale Depth Dataset\n    </h2>\n\n    <form nosubmit\n          [formGroup]="requestForm"\n          (ngSubmit)="onSubmit()">\n      <div class="mb3">\n        <div class="flex items-center">\n          <label class="font-semi-bold">Full name</label>\n          <div class="h6 right-align ml-auto">Required</div>\n        </div>\n        <input class="field block"\n               type="text"\n               formControlName="name">\n      </div>\n\n      <div class="mb3">\n        <div class="flex items-center">\n          <label class="font-semi-bold">Email address (official email from company or institution)</label>\n          <div class="h6 right-align ml-auto">Required</div>\n        </div>\n        <input class="field block"\n               [class.pale-red]="!validEmail"\n               type="text"\n               formControlName="email">\n      </div>\n\n      <div class="mb3">\n        <h2 class="font-semi-bold fs14">Mapillary Object Dataset Research Use License\n          <a class="neon-green block h4 align-middle text-decoration-none font-regular"\n             href="/dataset/assets/mapillary-object-dataset-research-use-license-2019.pdf"\n             target="_blank"\n             rel="noopener noreferrer">Download license PDF</a>\n        </h2>\n        <div class="p1 border-radius-4 border border-light-gray mt1 mb2"\n             style="border: 1px solid #D7DADD; height: 130px; overflow-y: scroll;">\n          <p class="block m0 p0 h5"\n             style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Mapillary Object Dataset Research Use License\n\n            Mapillary AB ("Mapillary") has developed, at considerable expense and effort, a collection of annotated street-level images formatted to facilitate use for the purpose of training AI systems and neural networks ("Object Dataset"). Mapillary is willing to license the use of this Object Dataset pursuant to the terms of this Mapillary Object Dataset Research Use License ("License") to you only if you obtained the Object Dataset directly from Mapillary, and only upon the condition that you accept all of the terms contained in this License. Exercising the rights granted to you below constitutes your agreement to be bound by the terms of this License. The term "you" and "your" means the individual using the Object Dataset, or clicking "accept" or "agree" or otherwise demonstrating acceptance of this License, and thereby becoming bound by it, and the company or other legal entity represented by such individual or on whose behalf such individual acts, and all affiliates thereto.\n\n            1. Research Use License Grant.\n\n            (a) Subject to and conditioned upon your compliance with the obligations of this License, Mapillary grants to you a worldwide, royalty-free, non-sublicensable, non-transferable, and non-exclusive copyright and database rights license, solely in furtherance of your Research Purpose, to download, reproduce and use the Object Dataset. Mapillary grants no rights to and you shall not in whole or in part: (1) create "Derivatives" (defined as derivative works, modifications, adaptations, or compilations of the Object Dataset or new images or labels derived from the Object Dataset), or (2) display or distribute the Object Dataset or Derivatives or (3) incorporate the Object Dataset or Derivatives in any publicly available product, service, software or technology.\n\n            (b) The term "Research Purpose" means use solely in conjunction with (1) internal non-published research projects and (2) publicly available research publications and studies, access to which is not subject to payment. The term "Research Purpose" excludes without limitation the creation of Derivatives or use in connection with the development of any product, service, software or technology or any commercial undertaking. Mapillary offers Object Dataset commercial use and Derivatives licenses per a separate license agreement. You shall not use the Object Dataset for any non-Research Purpose except as separately agreed with Mapillary in a signed writing. Such activity is not licensed or authorized under this License, and if undertaken may result in pursuit of all available remedies for intellectual property rights (including copyright and database rights) infringement, the availability of which you hereby acknowledge.\n\n            (c) The Object Dataset constitutes Mapillary\'s confidential information protected by intellectual property laws and treaties, and is licensed, not sold. All rights not expressly granted in this section 1 are reserved to Mapillary. No other right or license will be implied by conduct or otherwise. Mapillary and/or its licensors retain all right, title and interest in the Object Dataset and all associated intellectual property rights. Patents, trademark and servicemark rights, moral rights (including the right of integrity), publicity, privacy, and/or other similar personality rights are not licensed under this License.\n\n            (d) You shall not remove, destroy, deface or otherwise alter any legends, notices, statements or marks indicating Mapillary\'s ownership or the restrictions contained in this License.\n\n            (e) You shall not disclose or cause to be disclosed in whole or in part the Object Dataset or any information contained therein ("Confidential Information") to any third party or use Confidential Information except as specifically authorized by this License. You shall protect the confidentiality of Confidential Information with the same degree of care, but no less than reasonable care, as you use to protect your own confidential information of like nature. You shall ensure that only your staff members with a strict and essential need to use Confidential Information will receive access to Confidential Information.\n\n            (f) The rights of this section may be exercised solely by your employees and contractors, for the sole purpose of enabling such staff to assist you in your research. You shall enter into written agreements with such staff consistent with and no less protective of Mapillary and the Object Dataset than the terms of this License prior to disclosure of Object Dataset to such staff. Any services such staff perform in connection with the Object Dataset must be solely for your benefit on a work-made-for-hire basis, and such staff shall assign sole ownership and exclusive rights of any work product in connection with Object Dataset to you, without retaining use of, or any right, title or license of any kind to the Object Dataset. All such staff shall return to you or destroy all copies of or materials containing the Object Dataset in whole or in part upon the earlier of the end of such staffs\' performance of services to you or termination of this License.\n\n            (g) You shall notify Mapillary immediately when you become aware of any breach or violation of this License, or of any potential or actual infringement of intellectual property rights related to the Object Dataset.\n\n            2. Attribution. In a manner reasonably satisfactory to Mapillary, you shall cause to be conspicuously displayed in all public materials and websites referencing research conducted with the Object Dataset a notice that the research was conducted using the Object Dataset, with a link to the Object Dataset website or mapillary.com. You hereby consent to Mapillary listing the name and logo of your organization on the Object Dataset website and other material describing the Object Dataset.\n\n            3. Feedback. You agree that Mapillary may freely use and exploit in perpetuity any feedback, requirements, recommendations, ideas, bug fixes, reviews, ratings, benchmarks, comments, suggestions, or improvements, that you, or any employee or agent thereof, may at any time disclose or submit to Mapillary relating to the Object Dataset for Mapillary\'s business purposes, including for product licensing, support and development, without any obligation or payment to you.\n\n            4. Data. You hereby consent to Mapillary\'s collection and use of anonymized data (including meta-data, analytical, diagnostic and technical data, and usage statistics) concerning or arising from your use of the Object Dataset in order to provide the functionality of and improve the Object Dataset, for product development and marketing purposes, to protect against spam and malware, and for verifying License compliance.\n\n            5. Updates. Updates are subject to this License unless other terms accompany the updates. If so, those other terms will apply. Mapillary is not obligated to make any updates available, to continue making the Object Dataset available for any period of time, or to provide any technical support of any kind.\n\n            6. Compliance. You shall comply with all applicable laws, rules, and regulations in respect of the use of the Object Dataset.\n\n            7. Termination. Without prejudice to any other Mapillary rights or remedies, this License will automatically terminate if you fail to comply with its terms. In such event, you shall immediately destroy all copies and cease all use of the Object Dataset. You acknowledge and agree that breach of this License, or any unauthorized use or distribution of the Object Dataset, would cause irreparable harm to Mapillary, the extent of which would be difficult to ascertain, and that Mapillary will be entitled to seek without limitation immediate injunctive relief in any court of competent jurisdiction under the applicable laws thereof (and Mapillary\'s right to do so is not subject to arbitration). Mapillary may terminate this License, in whole or in part, upon written notice in the event the Object Dataset, in whole or in part, is in Mapillary\'s sole judgment subject to a claim of intellectual property rights infringement, violation of law or rights, or other claim impeding Mapillary\'s right or ability to grant the licensed rights hereunder.\n\n            8. Disclaimer. You acknowledge the Object Dataset may have inaccuracies, defects or deficiencies that may not be corrected by Mapillary. To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, Mapillary and its licensors provide the Object Dataset "as is" and with all faults, and disclaim all representations, warranties, and conditions, whether express, implied or statutory, including but not limited to representations, warranties and conditions related to: title, non-infringement, merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, accuracy or completeness, lack of defects, negligence or workmanlike effort, or correspondence to description. The entire risk arising out of use or performance of the Object Dataset remains with you.\n\n            9. Limitation of Liability. EXCLUDING ONLY DAMAGES ARISING OUT OF MAPILLARY\'S LIABILITY FOR FRAUD, DEATH OR PERSONAL INJURY CAUSED BY MAPILLARY\'S NEGLIGENCE, OR ANY OTHER LOSS FOR WHICH MAPILLARY CANNOT LAWFULLY EXCLUDE LIABILITY, MAPILLARY WILL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY DIRECT, INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL OR EXEMPLARY DAMAGES, OR COST OF PROCUREMENT OF SUBSTITUTE SERVICES, OR DAMAGES FOR LOSS OF REVENUE, PROFITS, GOODWILL, USE, DATA OR OTHER INTANGIBLE LOSSES (EVEN IF MAPILLARY HAS BEEN ADVISED OF THE POSSIBILITY OF SUCH DAMAGES), RESULTING FROM THE USE OF OR INABILITY TO USE THE OBJECT DATASET OR THE EXERCISE OF THE LICENSED RIGHTS GRANTED HEREUNDER.\n\n            10. Severability; Waiver; No Agency; Entire Agreement. If any of the provisions of this License are held to be in violation of applicable law, void, or unenforceable in any jurisdiction, such provisions will not affect the validity of the balance of the License, and such provisions are herewith waived or reformed to the extent necessary for the License to be otherwise enforceable in such jurisdiction. No waiver of any provision of this License will be deemed a further waiver or continuing waiver of such provision or any other provision, and Mapillary\'s failure to assert any right or provision under this License will not constitute a waiver of such right or provision. This License is the parties\' entire agreement relating to its subject matter and supersedes all prior or contemporaneous oral or written communications, proposals, negotiations, understandings, representations and warranties and prevails over any conflicting or additional terms of any quote, order or other communication between the parties relating to its subject matter.\n\n            11. Assignment. This License may and shall not be assigned or transferred, or its rights or obligations assigned or delegated, by you, in whole or in part, including by way of merger or reorganization, acquisition or otherwise, without the prior written consent of Mapillary. Any assignment made in violation of this section will be void. Mapillary may freely assign this License without the necessity for consent.\n\n            12. Governing Law; Arbitration.\n\n            (a) This License will be governed by and construed under the laws of Sweden. The choice of law rules of any jurisdiction, and the United Nations Convention on Contracts for the International Sale of Goods, will not apply. Any disputes between or claims brought by you or Mapillary arising out of or related to this License or the Object Dataset (including tort as well as contract claims, and whether pre-contractual or extra-contractual, as well as the arbitrability of any disputes (subject to section 12(b) below) shall be referred to and finally settled exclusively by binding arbitration before the International Court of Arbitration in accordance with the Rules of Arbitration of the International Chamber of Commerce in effect at the time of arbitration except as inconsistent with this section. The arbitration will be conducted by telephone, on-line and/or based solely upon written submissions where no in-person appearance is required. If in-person appearance is required, such hearings will be held in New York City, New York if you reside in or are headquartered in North or South America, or Malm\xf6, Sweden, if you reside or are headquartered anywhere else. The arbitrator will apply the law specified in this section. All awards may if necessary be enforced by any court having jurisdiction. The existence of any dispute, the existence or details of the arbitration proceeding, and all related documents, materials, evidence, judgments and awards therein, shall be kept confidential. Except as required by law, no party will make any public announcements with respect to the proceeding or the award, except as required to enforce same. The parties hereby waive the right to a trial by jury and agree to only bring claims in an individual capacity and not as a plaintiff or class member in any purported class or representative proceeding. All disputes will be arbitrated only on an individual basis and not in a class, consolidated or representative action. The arbitrator does not have the power to vary these provisions. All claims (excluding requests for injunctive or equitable relief) between the parties must be resolved via arbitration in accordance with this section. Should either party file an action contrary to this section, the other party may recover lawyers\' fees and costs associated with enforcing this section, provided that the party seeking the award has notified the other party in writing of the improperly filed claim, and the other party has failed to withdraw the claim in a timely fashion.\n\n            (b) Notwithstanding the foregoing, nothing in this section 12 will preclude the right and ability to bypass arbitration and file and maintain at any time an action for recovery of injunctive or provisional relief in any court of competent jurisdiction under the laws applicable thereto, and either party\'s right to do so is not arbitrable.\n\n            (c) A party prevailing in any litigation or arbitration related to this License or the Object Dataset will be entitled, in addition to such other relief as may be granted, to an award of reasonable attorneys\' fees.\n\n\n            end\n\n        </div>\n        <div>\n          <label class="semi-bold mr1">I agree to these terms</label>\n          <input type="checkbox"\n                 formControlName="agreed">\n          <p>\n            By agreeing to these terms or downloading the Mapillary Planet-Scale Depth Dataset, you and your organization agree and consent to:\n            <br> - the collection and use of personal information and data as set forth in the\n            <a class="neon-green text-decoration-none"\n               href="https://www.mapillary.com/privacy"\n               target="_blank"\n               rel="noopener noreferrer">Privacy Policy</a>;\n            <br> - the Mapillary Object Dataset Research Use License; and\n            <br> - the obligation to maintain the confidentiality of the Mapillary Planet-Scale Depth Dataset.\n          </p>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div *ngIf="!submitted"\n           class="pb3 flex justify-end">\n        <button [disabled]="!requestForm.valid || submitting ||\xa0!validEmail"\n                class="align-middle bg-neon-green block btn md-inline-block shadow shadow-hover white border-radius-4">\n          <span class="align-middle"\n                *ngIf="!submitting">Download</span>\n\n          <span class="align-middle"\n                *ngIf="submitting">Requesting download...</span>\n        </button>\n      </div>\n      <div *ngIf="submitted"\n           class="pb3 neon-green fs16">\n        <div>\n          <div>Thank you for submitting a download request! Download links will be provided via email shortly.</div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n    </form>\n  </section>\n</app-fullscreen-modal>\n',styles:[OZ()]})],cv);var Wne=C(71),Qne=C.n(Wne);let dv=class{};dv=Ie([$t({template:'<msls-header activeLink="citation"></msls-header>\n<section id="citation">\n  <div id="citation-top"\n       class="flex items-center flex-column mx-auto px3 py3 md-py4 width-100"\n       style="max-width: 840px">\n    <h1 class="fs42 font-bold black mt0">Citation</h1>\n    <div id="citation-content"\n         class="md-mt4 flex flex-column">\n      <div id="citation-paper"\n           class="mb3 mx-auto">\n        <a href="https://research.mapillary.com/img/publications/CVPR20c.pdf"></a>\n        <div></div>\n        <div></div>\n        <div></div>\n      </div>\n      <div class="md-ml4">\n        <h2 class="fs24 black font-bold mt0">Mapillary Street-Level Sequences: A Dataset for Lifelong Place Recognition</h2>\n        <p class="gray">\n          F. Warburg, S. Hauberg, M. Lopez-Antequera, P. Gargallo, Y. Kuang, and J. Civera. Mapillary Street-Level Sequences: A Dataset for Lifelong Place Recognition.\n          <br />\n          In Conference on Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (CVPR), 2020\n        </p>\n        <div class="flex">\n          <a href="https://research.mapillary.com/img/publications/CVPR20c.pdf"\n             class="text-decoration-none neon-green font-semi-bold">Research paper</a>\n          <div class="VerticalSeparator mx2"></div>\n          <a href="https://research.mapillary.com/img/publications/CVPR20c.bib"\n             class="text-decoration-none neon-green font-semi-bold">bib</a>\n          <div class="VerticalSeparator mx2"></div>\n          <a href="https://research.mapillary.com/img/publications/CVPR20c_supp.pdf"\n             class="text-decoration-none neon-green font-semi-bold">Supplementary material</a>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</section>\n<footer class="dark-grey py4 center">\n  Mapillary AB &copy; 2021\n</footer>\n',changeDetection:Jn.OnPush,styles:[Qne()]})],dv);var Yne=C(465),Kne=C.n(Yne);let hv=class{};hv=Ie([$t({template:'<msls-header activeLink="dataset"></msls-header>\n<div class="LandingBackground bg-cover bg-center black font-regular">\n  <div class="Container1200 px3 mx-auto flex items-center justify-between mobile-flex-column tablet-flex-column width-100">\n    <div class="flex flex-column mobile-center"\n         style="max-width:512px">\n      <div class="">\n        <h1 class="fs42 m0 font-bold mobile-fs24 mb24"\n            style="max-width:400px">Mapillary Street-level Sequences Dataset</h1>\n      </div>\n      <p class="fs20 gray m0 font-regular mobile-mt3 mb24">The largest and most diverse dataset for lifelong place recognition from image sequences in urban and suburban settings.</p>\n      <p class="black fs16 m0 pb24">\n        This Mapillary Street-level Sequences Dataset is provided under the\n        <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/"\n          target="_blank"\n          rel="noopener noreferrer"\n          class="text-decoration-none">\n          Creative Commons Attribution NonCommercial Share Alike (CC BY-NC-SA)\n        </a>\n        license.\n      </p>\n      <div class="flex mobile-justify-center">\n          <dataset-download-request\n            [datasetName]="\'Street-level Sequences\'"\n            [datasetType]="\'msls\'">\n          </dataset-download-request>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class="bg-white black rounded py24 px3 mobile-mt3 mb1"\n         style="box-shadow: 0px 4px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1); max-width: 512px">\n      <div class="mb2 black fs16 bold">Features</div>\n\n      <div class="flex items-start mb1">\n        <i class="circle-checkmark icon-16 neon-green mr1 mt1"></i> More than 1.6 million images\n      </div>\n      <div class="flex items-start mb1">\n        <i class="circle-checkmark icon-16 neon-green mr1 mt1"></i> 30 major cities across six continents\n      </div>\n      <div class="flex items-center mb1">\n        <i class="circle-checkmark icon-16 neon-green mr1"></i> All images tagged with sequence information, and geo-located with GPS and compass angles\n      </div>\n      <div class="flex items-center mb1">\n        <i class="circle-checkmark icon-16 neon-green mr1"></i> Capture times spanning all seasons over a nine-year period\n      </div>\n      <div class="flex items-center mb3">\n        <i class="circle-checkmark icon-16 neon-green mr1"></i> Different weather, cameras, daylight conditions, and structural settings\n      </div>\n      <div class="flex">\n        <a href="https://research.mapillary.com/"\n           class="ResearchLink flex items-center text-decoration-none black">\n          Brought to you by Mapillary Research\n          <i class="inline-block icon-24 arrow-right neon-green"\n             style="margin-left:4px"></i>\n        </a>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<div class="Container1200 mx-auto px2 pb3">\n  <video autoplay\n         loop\n         muted\n         playsinline\n         #video\n         (canplay)="video.play()"\n         (loadedmetadata)="video.muted = true"\n         style="width:100%">\n    <source type="video/mp4"\n            src="/dataset/assets/video/localization_v2.mp4" />\n  </video>\n</div>\n\n<div class="Container1200 mx-auto px3 pb160">\n  <div class="black fs32 font-bold mb3 mobile-fs24">More about this dataset</div>\n  <div class="flex items-start justify-between mobile-flex-column fs16 black">\n    <div style="max-width: 540px;">\n      Mapillary Street-Level Sequences (MSLS) is the largest, most diverse dataset for place recognition, containing 1.6 million images in a large number of short sequences. Spanning 30 cities on six continents, the dataset covers different seasons, weather and daylight conditions, various camera types and viewpoints, diverse architectural and structural settings (such as roadworks), and different levels of dynamic objects present in the scenes (such as moving pedestrians or cars).\n      <br><br>\n      Each image comes with metadata and attributes relevant for further research: raw GPS coordinates, capture time, and compass angle, as well as attributes for day/night, and view direction (front-, back-, or side-facing).\n    </div>\n    <div class="mobile-mt3"\n         style="max-width: 540px;">\n      We have also run extensive benchmarks on our dataset with previous state-of-the-art methods for place recognition. The results show that training on MSLS improves performance due to the diversity of the dataset in geographical distribution, seasonal and temporal changes, and particularly day/night changes.\n      <br><br>\n      Thanks to its wide geographical reach, diversity in scene characteristics, and sufficient size for training neural networks with large capacity, MSLS is the best dataset for pushing the state of the art in visual place recognition and its applications in practical settings across the world.\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<div class="Container1200 mx-auto px2 mb4">\n  <div class="mx-auto center"\n      style="max-width: 540px;">\n    <div class="black fs32 font-bold mb40">Mapillary Street-level Sequences SDK</div>\n    <div class="fs16 black">\n      <a class="text-decoration-none"\n        target="_blank"\n        rel="noopener noreferrer"\n        href="https://github.com/mapillary/mapillary_sls">This SDK</a>\n        includes an implementation of a PyTorch Dataset which can be used for evaluation\n        (returning database and query images) or for training (returning triplets).\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<dataset-footer></dataset-footer>\n',styles:[Kne()]})],hv);var Jne=C(413),Zne=C.n(Jne);const tre=[{mapCaption:"Imagery distribution in Europe",mapImage:"/dataset/assets/mtsd/map/europe.jpg",imageCaption:"Stockholm, Sweden",image:"/dataset/assets/mtsd/image/Bh36Ed4HBJatMpSNnFTgTw.jpg"},{mapCaption:"Imagery distribution in North America",mapImage:"/dataset/assets/mtsd/map/north_america.jpg",imageCaption:"Santa Cruz, United States",image:"/dataset/assets/mtsd/image/f82itz69069z_LC7xM6UIA.jpg"},{mapCaption:"Imagery distribution in South America",mapImage:"/dataset/assets/mtsd/map/south_america.jpg",imageCaption:"Rio de Janeiro, Brazil",image:"/dataset/assets/mtsd/image/vA6SFt0y9RYIuJbD5EFDSw.jpg"},{mapCaption:"Imagery distribution in Asia",mapImage:"/dataset/assets/mtsd/map/asia.jpg",imageCaption:"Tokyo, Japan",image:"/dataset/assets/mtsd/image/Lj8XqyQvfaNC-qatiz0e5g.jpg"},{mapCaption:"Imagery distribution in Africa",mapImage:"/dataset/assets/mtsd/map/africa.jpg",imageCaption:"Maseru, Lesotho",image:"/dataset/assets/mtsd/image/jm7I1Z22iwg3NVVuAxnFzg.jpg"},{mapCaption:"Imagery distribution in Oceania",mapI